The paper deals with graph algorithms and their performance on subgraphs, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of graphs and their properties in the algorithms suggests that the paper could also belong to computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses optimization problems such as minimum spanning forest, global minimum cut, maximum matching, and minimum vertex cover, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT).
